description: Calavera, a fun loving 80's rocker chick, falls to her death in 1989 only to instantaneously awaken in the year 2012. Now essentially a super powered zombie, deteriorating day by day, and sharing her body with a mysterious entity, this most unlikely heroine may be our last hope as dark forces plot to destroy civilization as we know it!

Following their surprise encounter with the Aegyptian, Zakol, the Neanderthal king Kulkan and his companion Xotol return to the monolith of Ytza. Where, with the savage Moon Clan closing in on the city, they seek to renew their strength through the mind-bending trial of the Visionquest.
name: The Memory of Being, Part Four: Ritual of the Dead Sun

description: Free-spirited, thrill-seeking, interstellar adventurer, Kristarella, embarks upon a new quest when she is hired by the daughter of the galaxy's wealthiest man, who himself has mysteriously vanished.
When mayhem erupts at a traveling circus in Gotham City, it's up to Batgirl to stop none other than Harley Quinn!
name: Chapter 2

volume.name: Batman: Arkham Knight: Batgirl & Harley Quinn Special

description:
The Return of the KINGZ

Aw Yeah Comics presents The Mighty Super Kingz:

Since the dawn of time, King Zobiac, King Freebird, and King Shark Toothe have protected planet Earth from the forces of evil.

When their arch-nemesis Gorlock unleashes a giant Tyrannosaurus Rex on the streets of Grand City, naturally The Mighty Super Kingz are called into action!

Action, Adventure, Comedy and Horror await in this kid-friendly comic from cartoonist Scoot McMahon!

Let's Get Regal!!

Created by Scoot McMahon and Corey Barba

All Aces

The ancients of renown knew a secret that allowed them programmatic control of earth's magnetosphere. The information has been hidden and forbidden ever since that time. Modern science is about to rediscover the secrets and the chaos that comes with it.

In this sixth issue in the Electromagnate series a hero is born.
name: All Aces

Winner of the Grand Prise at France's Angouleme Comics Festival in 2009. In this dark rendition, a greedy Geppetto builds Pinocchio as a metallic weapon of war, while Jiminy Cockroach is a homeless squatter living the good life in Pinocchio's skull. Exquisite drawings by celebrated cartoonist Winshluss bring to life a rich tale of greedy fools, lust, sadness, redemption, and hope. Winshluss has perfected the wordless comic with artwork primarily done in pen and ink, and watercolor which switches to paint for larger splash panels.
name: HC

description:
Predator's Folly

Chapter 08 of Avaiyo, Vol. 03

Heading back to Brosha, Sekken and Iyo meet up with their guild, Emerald Moon. Reunions are cut short as a new crisis emerges that has the means to threaten the entire world. With little time to spare, they depart for Preminx...in hopes of heading off the Dark Legion. With Emerald Moon standing between two armies, it is their hope the Region of Preminx will not be soaked in blood.
name: Predator's Folly

description: Comic Shop News is comics' weekly newsletter. Each issue is full-color, 8-12 pages in length, and features CSNsider, news, and interviews. CSN has a complete monthly checklist (complete with PREVIEWS order numbers), plus exclusive CSN Hot Picks, 'Fab Firsts,' and a monthly checklist of all the first issues for the month!
All bets are off as our heroes try to survive the zombie invasion, while the killer closes in on his next victim.

Although Sister Long is becoming more comfortable with life as a full-time missionary in Japan, she still has some doubts about whether all the hard work will pay off. Her companion teaches her to have more faith and more fun.
name: Month 7: August

volume.name: DENDO: One Year and One Half in Tokyo

description:
Titan Transformed

The ancients of renown knew a secret that allowed them programmatic control of earth's magnetosphere. The information has been hidden and forbidden ever since that time. Modern science is about to rediscover the secrets and the chaos that comes with it.

In this fourth issue in the Electromagnate series an old man has a bad day then recovers a memory that triggers his return to former glory.
name: Titan Transformed

description:
Improvements

After a tumultuous start, Geedey realizes that although Dia may be obnoxious, she has a lot to teach him - and he's not ready to lose that opportunity. When Dia's presence becomes uncertain, Geedey realizes how important she's become. Meanwhile, the men and women of Project Cottontail take stock of the situation at home, as well as their own personal investments in a project that could decide the fate of millions as the world teeters on the brink of total collapse. This issue contains the complete second chapter of Follower, along with 7-page bonus story, "Standing With Victor."
name: Improvements

description:
City of Mercy

After responding to a 911 call at the bomb blast in the massive District 08 protest rally, Hex and Puck pick up not one, but two Drops. As this Gatecrasher crew hurtles through the streets of Palomar City, the identities of their patients and the dangers they pose become crystal clear.
name: City of Mercy

description: As they set out to find the kidnapped Aydis, Brynhild and Sigurd run into trouble at a local village. With a quiet friend's help, Aydis strikes a crucial blow against the enemy.
Max and Candy have broken up! Or have they...? Is this Elliot's chance to swoop in?
name: Chapter Four

description:
She Sells Sanctuary

The one where our heroes learn the true nature of Ed's power.

In "Mars Lander", Haley Possesses a scientist on a doomed planet Mars 3 billion years ago! While her colleague contemplates his faith, God prepares to reward that faith by using Haley to send him to a whole new world... EARTH! And in "Everywhen", Haley Lands in a church with a priest... and a question.
name: Mars Lander

description:
The Cold War pt. 3

With the arrival of Chrome and Quantum the Lightspeed Enforcers have evened the odds and continue to do battle with Cryogen and her army of Ice Soldiers.Who will prevail?
name: The Cold War Pt. 3

description:
The Super 8 Cycle

In the last issue Electrolyte and The Justice Purveyors locked forms with Electrolyte's nemesis, the powerful and sexy Cottonmouth.

Cottonmouth worked with Jack Wales to capture Electrolyte but when that situation looked like it might not pan out Wales hired Super 8 as a contingency plan.

Wales won't stop until he steals Electrolyte's powers like his did in Issue #1.
name: The Super 8 Cycle

volume.name: The Misadventures of Electrolyte and The Justice Purveyors

description:
Ratus Inmolatio

The children are told stories about a witch in a moving house.

But a witch is a frightful old crone! There's no way this young woman is evil...
name: Ratus Inmolatio

description:
Nenetl of the Forgotten Spirits #3

In Part Three, the spirit Nena explores the Miercoles Doll Factory, the tombified ruins of her family's legacy. Jonah, the third apprentice, sheds his duty to help her, only to find that trusting the dead may kill the living.
name: Part Three

description:
This Isn't Any Of Your Business

Eric finds himself trapped like a prisoner in his own home. Eden fears her relationship may come to an abrupt end. Dice confronts a ghost from the past. And Eve is the person at the centre of it all. How will this end?
name: This Isn't Any Of Your Business

description:
Like the first issue, the second installment of Rancid Milk Presents collects an assortment of gag strips, literary adaptations, and short stories that I've done here and there. However, a recurring theme of impermanence comes up in more than a few entries.

"I See Your Face Before Me" is a riff on the old-fashioned romance comics of the West and the shojo manga of the East. Also included are a few gag strips as well as comics adaptations of poetry written by Edgar Allan Poe, Lewis Carroll, and Percy Blythe Shelley.

Rounding things out is "The Great Below". I wrote that story after the passing of a loved one and it's a meditation upon the nature of death and grief.
"We are all but pawns of varied masters, whose whims are guided by baseness. All sheep without strength of character or presence of nature." Shepherd 8:33-34

While Rakshash tries his best to handle a troubled Dracula, Finn's team infiltrates the castle, and the con's various moving parts click into place. Unfortunately, Lillian's agenda threatens to derail the evening. In this fluid and deadly situation, all are working without a net. Suspense, humor, intense character moments and enthralling world-building ensues as the veil continues to lift on SILVER's rich and unique take on the Dracula mythology.

Once again it is time to prepare yourself for the arrival of something Wicked! Issue 11 features a cover by Matt Sandbrook who offers you a warm welcome to this year's issue.

The Golden Cannibal Girl

The latest issue of Douglas Noble's Strip For Me comic tells a new and complete seaside story, as five friends return to the holiday haunt of their childhoods. A brooding, brutal rumination on nostalgia, The Golden Cannibal Girl will stay with you long after you close the pages.
name: The Golden Cannibal Girl

description: Cody Tries to quit Space Potion cold turkey in this VERY SPECIAL issue of Task Force Rad Squad.

Ruxby the Bear Detective has been sent to The Corner, to think about what he did.

With its greatest cop boxed up in toy prison, the sweet city of Toyburg is overrun with playthings on the edge of madness - driven by a mysterious force, obsessed with the crimes of others.

Looking back on recent villainy, can Ruxby survive long enough in jail to figure out who framed him? Can Hazbrow hold Toyburg Police together long enough to turn the tide?

Return to Fluffy Noir in this Step Beyond Imagination.

The stories were created by Brett Uren (Kuzimu, The Vale), Cy Dethan (Cancertown, Indifference Engine), Janos Honkonen (Kaiken yll etana, The Rocket Man from the Sea), co-editor Glenn Mane (Fubar, Indie Comics Horror), Grainne McEntee (Apes 'n' Capes), Jon Scrivens (Little Terrors), Kieran Squires (The Hammer), Frank Martin (Modern Testament), Ronald Montgomery, JImmy Furlong (S**t Flingers), Peter Rogers & Jake Young. The artists include: Juan Romera (Strange Nation), Mike Motz (Little JImmy Says 'Same is Lame'), Jon Scrivens (Little Terrors), Andrew Hartmann (S**t Flingers), Renzo Rodriguez (Toxic Storm), Lee Killeen (Under a Pale Blue Sky), Giles Crawford (Lowlives), Edward R. Norden (Murky Depths), Carlos Zamudio (The Remains), Charlie Hogg (The Hammer), Harold Saxon, Faye Harmon (Kuzimu, The Vale), Jimmy Kerast & the almighty Hal Laren (Reaper Comics). Letterers Nic Wilkinson (Cancertown, White Knuckle) & Mick Schubert (Memoirs of the Mysterious, Deviants) bring words into playful, animated life.
name: All Stitched Up

description:
Out Of The Attic Two

Hello Teddy Bear Fans! Tristan the Teddy Bear and the Cuddly Defenders are back with their second comic book anthology adventure - Out Of The Attic #2. This 32-page full-color Teddy Bear Adventure Comic continues all the Cuddly Defenders stories from the FIRST ISSUE of Out Of The Attic, as our Heroes continue to thwart to dastardly plans of the Boogeyman.

The ISSUE TWO contains FIVE NEW Comic/Illustrated stories that expand the adventures of everyone's favorite Cuddly Defender Creative Team of Nick Davis, Dan Nokes, Keir Knikia Lyles, Scott Markley, Jeana Byrd-Davis, Veronica Smith and Josh Lyman.

The Stories

Strange Lands by Nick Davis, Art Dan Nokes - sucked through the crack in the Great Reality Wall. Tristan the Teddy Bear finds himself in a strange place as he chases the Blue Skin Shaman Ex Cearula through an oddly familiar landscape

A Long Tall Tail by Jeana Byrd-Davis, Art Veronica Smith - How did Wilma and Fernando first met? Shocking origins, high adventures and more are explored in this wacky little tale that is full of heart.

Forrest & Scout by Scott Markley, Art Keir Knikia Lyles - Our clueless heroes start their quest to find their girls lost toys, on the shores of the ball pit sea in the Hunt for Red November.

The Menace of Mech-A-Nor by Dan Nokes - Driven from their homes by the rampaging Mech-A-Nor, the residents of Second Chance turn to the most reluctant of Cuddly Defenders Fernando the Mouse Lion to help them,

Helping Hand by Nick Davis, Art Keir Knikia Lyles - Artie the Teddy Bear is really not having a good night as he tries to keep his child's secret treasure box safe from a mysterious menace.
name: Out Of The Attic Two

description:
Hunter's Moon Pt. 2

Enter the Crimson Mask! Virgin finally meets her match but this new adversary may prove to be her undoing as the Wolfen take to the black forest to hunt for her and Hania.
name: Hunter's Moon Part 2

description: The 32 page Handbook profiles all of the major characters in the Advent Universe. This is the perfect jump-on point for new readers of Advent Comics titles. This goes hand-in-hand with other Advent comic publications.

2012 was a spectacular year for CBLDF, with victory in the Ryan Matheson case, clearing the name of an American citizen who was arrested for the comics on his laptop; a $60,000 donation from the Gaiman Foundation to pay for an expanded education program; Banned Books Week and sponsorship of the Kids Right to Read Project; and much, much more. But with recent book challenges and the removal of books such as Alan Moore's Neonomicon from libraries, it's obvious CBLDF still has a lot of work to do.

In 2013, CBLDF successfully stood up to every First Amendment emergency we faced. We also made serious contributions to education with publications, articles, lectures, and appearances that reached communities around the world. Thanks to the support of our donors, CBLDF is reaching a wider audience than ever in our mission to defend the freedom to read comics.

CBLDF's important work made huge strides in 2014! From leading a comics-focused Banned Books Week and expanding our education program, to fighting the rising tide of censorship in schools and providing legal aid in a wide range of comics-oriented cases, CBLDF's efforts are more timely than ever. CBLDF works hard to stop censorship in its tracks, with legal experts on call to manage every First Amendment emergency.

In the CBLDF Annual Report 2015, we're proud to provide you a brief snapshot of our efforts defending the freedom to read in 2015! This year saw the most attacks on the freedom to read comics in a generation, including calls to ban graphic novels in schools and libraries, threatened legal actions, and unconstitutional legislation that endangers the rights of creators, retailers, and readers. CBLDF responded to all of these threats with timely direct assistance, expert legal action, and a deep, prevention-minded education program.
